{#
  Health Check Routes
  
  APISIX provides built-in health endpoints via the Status API server (port 7085):
    - GET /status       → Liveness probe (returns {"status":"ok"})
    - GET /status/ready → Readiness probe (returns 200 after config loaded)
  
  These are available at http://127.0.0.1:7085 and should be used for
  Kubernetes liveness/readiness probes.
  
  Kubernetes probe configuration:
    readinessProbe:
      httpGet:
        path: /status/ready
        port: 7085
      periodSeconds: 10
      timeoutSeconds: 2
      failureThreshold: 3
    
    livenessProbe:
      httpGet:
        path: /status
        port: 7085
      periodSeconds: 10
      timeoutSeconds: 2
      failureThreshold: 3
  
  If you need a health endpoint on the proxy port (e.g., for external load balancers),
  uncomment the route below. It uses the mocking plugin to return 200 without
  touching any upstream.
  
  See: https://apisix.apache.org/docs/apisix/stand-alone/#enable-status-api
#}

